  "texts": [
    "During the procedure, she is found to have a dark discoloration of the entire colon with lymph follicles shining through as pale patches.",
    "What is the most likely underlying etiology?",
    "Options: (A) Drinking lots of prune juice (B) Colon cancer (C) Laxative abuse (D) Normal anatomic variation (E) Inflammatory bowel disease Answer: (C) Explanation: The dark discoloration is a result of lipofuscin in macrophages and not melanin.",
    "This patient most likely has melanosis coli, also known as pseudomelanosis coli, secondary to laxative abuse.",
    "This benign condition is often discovered incidentally during colonoscopy and is considered a disorder of pigmentation of the colonic wall."
